intro: Cyathodes fraseri, commonly known as the Fraser's cyathodes, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Myrtaceae, which includes eucalyptus and other aromatic plants. Cyathodes fraseri is often found in heathlands and open forests, thriving in well-drained soils.
